The paper deals with the problem of aggregating noisy labels provided by a set of heterogeneous annotators in crowdsourcing, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also takes into account annotator reliability and label dependency, which are important factors in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with unsupervised multi-label annotation aggregation, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
